## Limitations

The findings presented are based on available literature and may not encompass all aspects of the relationship between intelligence and anxiety. Some studies may have methodological limitations or biases that could affect their conclusions. Additionally, the complexity of human psychology means that individual differences and external factors can influence the correlation between intelligence and anxiety, making it difficult to generalize findings across all populations. Further research is needed to explore these nuances and provide a more comprehensive understanding of the topic.